    "ocr_text": "X.

Apr. 12, 1910.

Mr. H. B. Perham, President,

Order of Railroad Telegraphers,

Star Building, St. Louis, Mo.

Dear Sir and Brother:

I am just in receipt of a letter from Mr. Fred L. Frick
of Garrett, Indiana, in which he says:

"My attention has been called to the fact that there are
at the present time a great many telephone and semaphore men on the
B. & O. Railroad Stations who are desirous of joining an Organization.
I wish you would, by return mail, advise me what Organization
they would be entitled to go into, or whether or not they
could perfect an organization of their own along this system."

Before making any reply thereto, I would like your advice
as to whether your international union is prepared to accept these
men into membership, or whether they should become directly affiliated to the A. F. of L.?

Thanking you in advance for your prompt reply, I am,

Fraternally Yours,

President,

American Federation of Labor.",
